3. Social Engineering Tactics
Phishing is just one part of social engineering, where attackers exploit human psychology. Common tactics:

Pretexting: Pretending to be someone you trust (e.g., IT helpdesk).

Baiting: Offering something tempting (e.g., a free gift) to get you to click.

Tailgating: Physically following you into restricted areas.

Quishing: Sending QR codes that lead to malicious links.





